      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: smooth providers settings tab switching without waiting on resize",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nSmooth settings tab switching around the providers pane by decoupling tab\r\nselection from window resizing and reducing eager sidebar work.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n - Updated `Sources/CodexBar/PreferencesView.swift`\r\n - Switched settings tab selection to a custom binding that commits the\r\n  selected tab immediately\r\n - Suppressed duplicate layout updates when the custom binding already handled\r\n  a tab change\r\n - Scheduled the animated window resize after selection is committed so the\r\n  clicked tab responds right away\r\n - Updated `Sources/CodexBar/PreferencesProvidersPane.swift`\r\n - Added a lightweight sidebar subtitle path for provider rows\r\n - Kept the richer provider presentation for the selected provider detail view\r\n  only\r\n\r\n## Why\r\n\r\nSwitching into providers previously felt delayed because the app did provider\r\nsidebar work and resized the settings window before the new tab visibly\r\nopened. Switching out of providers also felt better when the tab change\r\nhappened before the resize, so this applies that interaction model\r\nconsistently.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\n- Ran `swift test --filter ProvidersPaneCoverageTests`\r\n- Swift Testing reported 27 tests in 1 suite passed\r\n- Ran `make check`",
